*''[[Flying Yankee]]''<U+2014>A very similar streamlined trainset that operated on the [[Boston and Maine Corporation|Boston and Maine Railroad]]; it is undergoing restoration to operating condition as of 2006.
*''[[Nebraska Zephyr]]''<U+2014>Another of Burlington's ''Zephyr'' fleet, one example of which is preserved at the [[Illinois Railway Museum]].
*"[[Fliegender Hamburger]]" ("Flying Hamburger")<U+2014>a German diesel trainset entering service in 1933, performing regularly at speeds of up to 100&nbsp;mph (160&nbsp;km/h).
*[[ETR 200]]-Italian high speed electric train.
