==Further reading==
*{{cite book| author=Byron, Carl R.| title=Pioneer Zephyr : America<U+2019>s First Diesel-Electric Stainless Steel Streamliner| publisher=Heimburger House Publishing| month=January | year=2006| isbn=0-911581-58-8 }}
*{{cite book| author=Morgan, David P.| title=Diesels West| publisher=Kalmbach Publishing| location=Milwaukee, Wisconsin| year=1963| id=LCCN 62019987}} Chronicle of the rise of diesel power on the Burlington with specific emphasis on the Pioneer Zephyr, its record-setting run, and its descendants.
*{{cite book| author=Rediske, R. W.| title=The Pioneer Zephyr| publisher=Authorhouse| year=2002| isbn=1-4033-5125-2}} The author of this book was a passenger aboard the "Dawn-to-Dusk" run in 1934.

